 }}</ref>比方说，试图学习少数语言的人们可能会阅读用多数语言写成的典籍并止步于此，结果导致说少数语言的人不增反减<ref name="New ways to revitalise minority language: the impact of the Internet in the case of Aragonese">{{cite journal |first=Santiago Jorge Paricio |last=Martín |first2=Juan Pablo Martinez |last2=Cortés |url=http://www.uoc.edu/ojs/index.php/digithum/article/viewDownloadInterstitial/n12-paricio-martinez/n12-paricio-martinez-eng |title=New ways to revitalise minority language: the impact of the Internet in the case of Aragonese |journal=Digithum: the Humanities in the Digital Era |issue=12 |date=May 2010 |publisher=UOC |accessdate=2010-11-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100815002618/http://www.uoc.edu/ojs/index.php/digithum/article/viewDownloadInterstitial/n12-paricio-martinez/n12-paricio-martinez-eng |archivedate=2010-08-15 }}</ref>同时，人们可能鼓励那些原本说少数语言的人去学习多数语言，以便能够上网去寻求更多的资源，结果导致自己原本所使用的语言的流失。<ref name="English as a global language">{{cite book
| first = David
| last = Crystal
| title = English as a Global Language
| url = https://archive.org/details/englishasgloball0000crys_j7o0
| location = Cambridge
| publisher = [[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]
| year= 2003
 }}</ref>人们仍需进一步观察那些濒危少数语言的未来在互联网上的传播。

